  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A microgreen is a young edible plant harvested after the [cotyledons](../../../terms/cotyledon.md) have expanded and just as the first true leaves begin to appear, typically seven to twenty-one days after planting. Microgreens are grown in shallow [trays](./tray.md) with a thin layer of growing medium and are cut at the stem just above the soil line.",
